# Speedrail Core Features

## Context
- When setting up new Speedrail features
- When working with core Speedrail dependencies
- When configuring Speedrail components

## Requirements
- Use standard Speedrail gem stack
- Follow proper configuration patterns
- Implement proper environment settings
- Use recommended testing frameworks
- Follow security best practices

## Examples
<example>
```ruby
# Proper Gemfile configuration
source "https://rubygems.org"
gem "rails", "~> 7.0.0"
gem "devise" # Authentication
gem "activeadmin" # Admin panel
gem "delayed_job" # Background jobs
gem "rspec-rails" # Testing
gem "rubocop" # Code style
gem "faker" # Test data
```
</example>

